        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Tribal Internet Expansion Act of </b><strong>2021</strong></p> <p>This bill extends to Indian reservations, dependent Indian communities, Indian allotments, and areas with high populations of Indians the universal service principle that telecommunications and information services in rural, insular, and high cost areas should be available at rates that are reasonably comparable to urban areas.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
